<br>
The Ring of Mystic Souls in inviting all adventurers of season 45-52 to join our crusade against Lord Nagafen. We will launch the assault on November 22. The forces will assemble at the druid ring in Lavastorm BEFORE 2pm EST. First groups will head towards Nagafen's Lair at noon. We most likely will have a force ready to assist in clearing our path. In case we believe we lack the power to slay the dragon the raid will be cancelled.<br>
<br>
To join us you must have appropriate dragon-fighter gear ((MR and FR resistance)) and sign up below.<br>
<br>
(ooc)<br>
<br>
LOOT POLICY:<br>
<br>
All items will be rolled on Need-before-Greed basis, meanining that all those who can and will use an item can roll /random 1000. Loot will be splitted after the raid inside the lair. <br>
<br>
BASIC STRATEGY:<br>
<br>
1. All please join chat Nagafenraid - all chat should go there, preferably role-playing . The raid channel is for important messages only, if you are unsure what is important, use chat.<br>
<br>
2. Stick to your group. If you have questions or problems contact the groupleader. <br>
<br>
3. Elemental blankets, runed daggers and elemental defenders will most likely be available before the raid. If your MR is lower than 100 (unbuffed) you will spend most of the time feared. If your FR is too low you will die quickly. Consider buying holy cake and Kaladim's Constitutional - they are a great way to improve your resistances.<br>
<br>
4. Once the groups are assembled the raid will start moving towards the Throne Room. A separate team will slay the giants to clear the path. We will not do raid-scale buffing till we reach the so-called &quot;prep-room&quot;. Ask your group mates for help with buffing - toughest thing you will face on path to the &quot;prep-room&quot; will be lava crawlers.<br>
<br>
<br>
5. Once we reach the large corridor before the &quot;prep-room&quot; all groups will stop and the buffing group will assemble. Ask your group memebrs to cast some junk buffs on you - order of buffs is no longer important. &quot;Junk buffs&quot; include: all kinds of vision enhancement, resistances to disease, poison and cold, enduring breath and many others. Then groups will proceed one by one and receive a hp buff, haste and resist buff. Shaman buff's are useful, we will try to provide them as well, but no guarantees here. KEI, clarity and such are not important during the dragon fight, but maigcs that increase the mana pool are useful. Buffing must be done as efficiently as possible - buffs will not be recasted! Try filling 14 buff slots before the fight, always leave the 15th free.<br>
<br>
6. Once buffed sit by the wall near your group leader. Switch run to walk, so you do not wander away far when feared. If you have resistant discipline prepare it.<br>
<br>
7. When buffing is done we will proceed to the dragon lair immediately. All but one group will attack Nagafen, one group will fight the Magus. Use /disc resistant when entering the lair.<br>
<br>
8. The main assist group will head inside 3 seconds before the rest. Initial healing will be performed using the Lay on Hands power of paladins.<br>
<br>
9. Unless you are the MA , stay under the tail of the dragon - this way you will avoid his breath. Do not taunt! If you are a melee fighter keep hitting him like there is no tomorow right the moment you get near him.<br>
<br>
10. Nagafen does not use any spells. All magic slingers should simply <br>
start blasting when he is down to 70-60% health. You MUST be in melee range to land a spell on him! Forget about casting fire based spells, magic is often resisted but cold seems to work. Stay under his tail.<br>
<br>
11. If you are feared, wait patiently till the effect wears off and rush back into the lair - we fight till the last of us or Nagafen fall. If we all die we will organise coffins and go back to the entrance of Nagafens Lair.<br>
<br>
12 If we win, the raid leader or nominated looter will take the stuff from the dragon, we will split it all and then porters will get us out.<br>
<br>
<br>
To win we need at least 25 adventurers for the final fight, preferably 30 or more. Two clerics are a bare minimum as well as 3 bards. Without them we stand no chance.<br>
<br>
Please post below if you are interested in attending. We look forward to seeing you on the 22nd!!<br>
<br>
