 purchase Holy Cakes and Kaladim Constituationals in the bazaar. These food/drink items will boost your stats fire/magic +5 each I believe. Basically I have been earning my pp these last few weeks and doing little adventuring so that I can purchase proper gear. If you can get your stats close enough hopefully we will be able to get some nice summoned gear to push you to the appropriate levels. It also looks like we have a few bards who will be coming along and they have many wonderful songs that will help our resists!! Hope this helps feel free to seek me out if I can assist you! <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=luinefv>Luinefv</A> at: 11/18/03 6:12 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wargus>Wargus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/18/03 7:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=781.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help before the raid</span><hr size=1> *The young warrior walks into the meeting hall and heads straight for the main table.*  I am Wargus, proud warrior of the Storm.  I hear that the dragon is going to meet his death soon.  *a small but evil grins begins to form on the young warrior*  I will be there.   I will challange anyone for the right to be the main fighter in this battle.  I seek no riches from his death.  His lair of wealth does not concern me. I only wish to see him die.<br>
